	(text "- Compare charger ICs\n- Check circuits\n- Choose passive conponent values\n- Connect the LED and Switch matrices. Assign LEDs to each inputs.\n- Select PCB foot prints\n\nI feel that my power and ground levels are confusing\n\nSchematic\n- Refactor Schematic to r/PrintedCircuitBoard Guide\n- Refactor the root schematic to show how the system is connected\n	- I want to add logic levels and ground differentiation\n	- I want custom grapics for each symbol\n- Refactor chip configurations to explain my choices\n- Rename all the component references so they are grouped and easier to layout\n- Select actual components, footprints, 3D models for all components\n- Pass those design reviews softwares\n\nPCB\n- generate and recreate ergonomic montary key layout in PCB\n- determine latch layout on PCB"
